The paper deals with the characterization of complexity classes, specifically PTIME, in terms of ordinary differential equations. This falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses continuous-time models of computation, which could fall under the categories of dynamical systems (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and control systems (cs.SY).
